    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're working on a pet adoption app that stores info about each animal: their name, age, and whether they're already adopted.\r\n\r\n1. Look at the variables already defined: `pet_name`, `pet_age`, and `is_adopted`\r\n\r\n2. Try using different operations (`+`, `-`, etc.) on them.\r\n\r\n3. Predict which operations will work, and which will give you errors.\r\n\r\n4. Use `print()` to test and explore what happens.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYou can add numbers and combine strings — but some operations won't work with booleans or if the data types don't match. Try it and see what happens!",
